channel.name: `RuntimeError: unreachable` Error After Upgrading o1js Pack to 0.14 Version

messages.content:
Hi everyone, I've recently encountered an issue after upgrading my o1js pack to version 0.14, and I'm wondering if anyone else has experienced a similar issue.

The specific error I'm encountering is  `RuntimeError: unreachable`. This error occurs when I attempt to run my test script, and it seems to consistently appear around the middle of the script. Strangely, if I remove the first half of the script, the remaining portion runs without any issues.

This problem did not occur with version 0.13, where the entire script ran smoothly. I'm curious if anyone has insights into potential limits or changes in the 0.14 version that might be causing this behavior.
